		   <h2>Jared Nathaniel Yoder</h2>
		   <p id="aka">AKA: Charlie, Jrod, Jman and Jare Bear<br>
		      October 6, 1989 - April 17, 2012</p>
		   <p>On April 9, 2012 our family began a journey no family wants to take. Our amazing Jared, age 22, was involved in a horrible accident with a semi. While trying to pass a vehicle he was blinded by the rising sun 
		   and failed to complete the pass, hitting rear axles of the oncomiing tractor-trailer.  He was then air lifted to a local hospital where he was admitted into the intensive care unit with a severe 
		   <a href="https://medlineplus.gov/traumaticbraininjury.html">traumatic brain injury.</a></p> 
		   
		   <p>We spent the next 8 days by his side along with many family and friends. Unfortunately by day 8 it became obvious to us that he was very weary and was not going to be able to fight his way back to us. After talking through
		   it over as a family and talking to the doctor we released our wonderful Jared into the arms of God on April 17th, 2012.</p>
		   
		   <p>Our family believes in giving to others so it was no surprise that when Jared got his driver's license he designated to be an <a href="https://www.organdonor.gov/register.html">organ donor</a>. We are very proud 
		   of Jared and his decision to be an <a href="https://www.organdonor.gov/register.html">organ donor</a>. We hope to carry on Jared's legacy by encouraging <a href="https://www.organdonor.gov/register.html">organ donation</a> 
		   as well as doing what we can to see that no other family loses a loved one to <a href="https://medlineplus.gov/traumaticbraininjury.html">traumatic brain injury<a/>.</p>
		    
